    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 240\u00b0C/ 220\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 9 and boil half a kettle</p><p>Cut your <strong>potato[es]</strong> and <strong>sweet potato[es]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span></strong>(skins on) into chips and add them to a baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray[s] in the oven for 25-30 min or until crisp</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/indian-style-cod-n-chips-with-curry-sauce-and-peas/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Zest your <strong>lime[s]</strong> (try to grate lightly with a micro-plane or sharp box grater and avoid grating the white pith, as this is very bitter)</p><p>Add your <strong>cod fillet[s]</strong> to a bowl with a squeeze of <strong>lime juice </strong>(you'll use the rest later!), the <strong>lime zest</strong>, your <strong>black sesame seeds</strong>,<strong> ground turmeric</strong>, a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>marinated cod fillet[s]</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/indian-style-cod-n-chips-with-curry-sauce-and-peas/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Place the <strong>marinated cod fillet[s] </strong>on a separate <strong>tin foil</strong>-lined<strong> </strong>baking tray (or two!)</p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 12-15 min or until the fish is cooked through \u2013 this is your <strong>Indian-style cod</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked when it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/indian-style-cod-n-chips-with-curry-sauce-and-peas/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and grate (don't chop!) your <strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Peel and grate (don't chop!) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Dissolve your<strong> vegetable stock mix</strong>, <strong>cornflour </strong>and 2 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar </strong>in 75ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[115ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[150ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>and 75ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[115ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[150ml]</span> <strong>milk </strong>and whisk well \u2013 this is your <strong>cornflour mix</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/indian-style-cod-n-chips-with-curry-sauce-and-peas/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Chop your<strong> creamed coconut</strong> roughly (if required!)</p><p>Add your <strong>blanched peas</strong>, <strong>chopped creamed coconut</strong>, a small splash of <strong>cold water</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>to a large heatproof bowl</p><p>Cover the bowl with <strong>cling film</strong> and pierce a few holes in the top</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/indian-style-cod-n-chips-with-curry-sauce-and-peas/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Put the bowl in the <strong>microwave</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until the peas are hot</p><p>Once hot, mash the peas with a squeeze of<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><strong>lime</strong> <strong>juice </strong>until they come together nicely \u2013 these are your <strong>coconut</strong> <strong>mushy peas</strong></p><p>Cut the <strong>remaining lime</strong> into 1 wedge per person</p><p>Chop your <strong>coriander</strong> finely, including the stalks</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/indian-style-cod-n-chips-with-curry-sauce-and-peas/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>grated ginger</strong>, <strong>grated garlic</strong> and your <strong>curry powder</strong> and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>cornflour mix </strong>and cook for 2-3 min or until reduced and glossy \u2013 this is your <strong>chip shop curry sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/indian-style-cod-n-chips-with-curry-sauce-and-peas/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>Indian-style cod </strong>with the<strong> chips</strong>,<strong> coconut</strong> <strong>mushy peas </strong>and a little bowl of<strong> chip shop curry sauce </strong>to the side</p><p>Garnish with a<strong> lime wedge </strong>and <strong>chopped coriander</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
